        +refs('Mark 10:45; 1-Tim.2:6', 'and'): |Jesus is our #[em ransom] i.e. our Passover lamb, a #[em sin offering] to lead us to repentance.
      p Jesus is quoting
        +refs('Psa.22:1'): |on the cross.
        | The sacrificial animals in Leviticus were not being punished.
        | The Septuagint version of Isaiah 53:10 reads very differently to the Masoretic.
    +heresy(
      'Original Sin',
      'We are all born with a sinful nature inherited from Adam, guilty not innocent from birth. Unbaptised babies who die go to hell.',
      'Psa.51:5; John 3:6; Rom.5:12',
      'Augustine (influcenced by Gnosticsm)',
      'Allows sinners to blame God, not themselves, for their sins i.e. "God made me this way!", so God is unjust to judge them. Also leads to the unbiblical practice of infant baptism. Derives from Gnosticsm which says all flesh is evil.',
      'Deut.1:39, 24:16; Isaiah 7:15; Jer.19:4; Eze.18:19-20; Mat.18:2-5; John 9:41; Rom.9:11')
      :markdown-it
        God does not hold us accountable for Adam's sin, only our own.
    +heresy(
